Skyline & arrays For class, we have been reviewing arrays, and the teacher gave us practice programs. Those are located in the Array folder. As for skyline, previously there was a set width to the buildings. I decided I wanted to change to be more dynamic, so I set the building to change and for the windows to adapt to the sizes. also, there's now stars in the sky. :) :/ :P

Tracer, tictactoe game In the tracer class, lily gave me the idea to erase the line. My dad took it one step further. when clicked, the line has a sparkle as it is erased. Originally, in testing, the line was white, but changed to rainbow. As for the tic tac toe game, it is just that. When the mouse hovers over it, it shows a temporary symbol. On click, it registers the move, changes player, checks if someone wins if if cat's game, and then continues. Fun stuff. Yay! Sincerely, :/

Update to canvas and Skyline I tried making the stars move in the skyline class, but it sucked. too slow. As for canvas, I added a method to get the color at a certain point. may be useful. sincerely :/

Arrays and TicTacToe For class, we had to write programs involving arrays and arraylists Many involve looping. Found we can't switch refences of variables in methods. Also edited TicTacToe. It now can play against a computer. Not perfect, but pretty good. As well, more modular, so it looks prettier. Much less # of lines. that's all for now. -MJ :/

Major TicTacToe update YAY! TTT game can now be fully automatic I made the computer check situations better as well, more updates to random files w/ warnings. also, partner program is a test for school work. sincerely, :/

more class projects, improved TTT a lot of the update includes updates to files that were required for class. For example, the PartnerProgram repository is actually for a partner test, where I coded one section and someone else coded the other. In TTT, the computer has been tested a lot and verified. As well, it now loops back to the menu if not Computer vs Computer. well, that's all. adios farewell -MJ :/

(Attempt at keyboard, not successful) sincerely, MJ :/

Stars move and digits write For the skyline class, I decided to implement a star class that would control each star and set it to be a new thread in the processor. This allowed for the stars to move seperate to the timing of the main program and more independent. As well, for the digit and mail files, those were for APCS, where you converted a zip code into a series of | and :. sincerely, MJ :/

working with interfaces, connect 4 interface testing, including a dataset that computes max and mins of different classes. connect 4 is from last year, but still one of my most prized possessions. so good. working amazing. have fun with it. MJ :/

Inheritence This unit we focused on inheritence, including parent and child classes, extending classes, and whatnot. A bunch of examples for this too. Soon will be implementing some abstract classes. until next time. MJ :/

recursion This unit focused on recursion, and so we did some tests. This includes some practice programs,such as factorial and Fibonacci. I improved on Factorial by using an arraylist to hold my digits and using that as my value to get larger numbers. That should be all. Have a great day. MJ :/
